  "body": "Cinder-based dynamic PVs don't have a region label at the time of creation.\r\nBut PersistentVolumeLabelController in the cloud-controller-manager labels the PVs based on their region.\r\nCinder plugin should add the region label to the PVs at the time of creation regardless of cloud-controller-manager.\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n```\r\nkind: PersistentVolume\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: cinder-pv\r\n  labels:\r\n    failure-domain.beta.kubernetes.io/zone: nova\r\nspec:\r\n  capacity:\r\n    storage: 1Gi\r\n  accessModes:\r\n    - ReadWriteOnce\r\n```\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n```\r\nkind: PersistentVolume\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: cinder-pv\r\n  labels:\r\n    failure-domain.beta.kubernetes.io/zone: nova\r\n    failure-domain.beta.kubernetes.io/region: RegionOne\r\nspec:\r\n  capacity:\r\n    storage: 1Gi\r\n  accessModes:\r\n    - ReadWriteOnce\r\n```\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n/sig openstack",
